Parma loanee, Dejan Kulusevski has insisted that Real Madrid ace, Eden Hazard has performed better than Barcelona captain, Lionel Messi and Juventus forward, Cristiano Ronaldo in the last three years. The 19-year-old midfielder believes the Belgium international has been far superior to Messi and Ronaldo, adding that the former Chelsea star is the best player in the world. “For me, the best player in the world is Eden Hazard,” Kulusevski told La Repubblica. “With the ball, he does everything I want to do. “For the last three years at least, I think he performed better than Lionel Messi and Cristiano Ronaldo.” Hazard is yet to hit top form for Zinedine Zidane’s men since he joined the Los Blancos from Chelsea last summer. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.